defs.docs:
**arrayvec** provides the types `ArrayVec` and `ArrayString`: 
 array-backed vector and string types, which store their contents inline.

defs.name: Array
defs.docs: Trait for fixed size arrays.

defs.name: Item
defs.docs: The array’s element type

defs.name: Index
defs.docs: The smallest index type that indexes the array.

defs.name: ArrayString
defs.docs: A string with a fixed capacity.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new empty `ArrayString`.

defs.name: from
defs.docs: Create a new `ArrayString` from a `str`.

defs.name: from_byte_string
defs.docs: Create a new `ArrayString` from a byte string literal.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Return the capacity of the `ArrayString`.

defs.name: is_full
defs.docs: Return if the `ArrayString` is completely filled.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Adds the given char to the end of the string.

defs.name: try_push
defs.value: fn (&mut self, c: char) -> Result<(), CapacityError<char>>

defs.name: push_str
defs.docs: Adds the given string slice to the end of the string.

defs.name: try_push_str
defs.value: fn <'a> (&mut self, s: &'a str) -> Result<(), CapacityError<&'a str>>

defs.name: pop
defs.docs: Removes the last character from the string and returns it.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs: Shortens this `ArrayString` to the specified length.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes a `char` from this `ArrayString` at a byte position and returns it.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Make the string empty.

defs.name: set_len
defs.docs: Set the strings’s length.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Return a string slice of the whole `ArrayString`.

defs.name: RangeArgument
defs.docs:
`RangeArgument` is implemented by Rust's built-in range types, produced
 by range syntax like `..`, `a..`, `..b` or `c..d`.

defs.name: start
defs.docs: Start index (inclusive)

defs.name: end
defs.docs: End index (exclusive)

defs.name: element
defs.docs: Extract the overflowing element

defs.name: simplify
defs.docs: Convert into a `CapacityError` that does not carry an element.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Return the capacity of the `ArrayVec`.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs: Remove the last element in the vector and return it.

defs.name: swap_remove
defs.docs: Remove the element at `index` and swap the last element into its place.

defs.name: swap_pop
defs.docs: Remove the element at `index` and swap the last element into its place.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Remove the element at `index` and shift down the following elements.

defs.name: pop_at
defs.docs: Remove the element at `index` and shift down the following elements.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs:
Shortens the vector, keeping the first `len` elements and dropping
 the rest.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Remove all elements in the vector.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the elements specified by the predicate.

defs.name: set_len
defs.docs: Set the vector’s length without dropping or moving out elements

defs.name: drain
defs.docs:
Create a draining iterator that removes the specified range in the vector
 and yields the removed items from start to end. The element range is
 removed even if the iterator is not consumed until the end.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Return the inner fixed size array, if it is full to its capacity.

defs.name: dispose
defs.docs: Dispose of `self` without the overwriting that is needed in Drop.

defs.name: as_slice
defs.docs: Return a slice containing all elements of the vector.

defs.name: as_mut_slice
defs.docs: Return a mutable slice containing all elements of the vector.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: By-value iterator for `ArrayVec`.

defs.name: Drain
defs.docs: A draining iterator for `ArrayVec`.
